# ========================================
# SECURITY NOTES - IMPORTANT!
# ========================================
# 1. NEVER commit .env file to version control
# 2. Use strong, unique values for all keys (minimum 32 characters)
# 3. Rotate keys regularly (every 90 days recommended)
# 4. Use different keys for development and production
# 5. For Gmail EMAIL_PASS, use App Password (not your regular password)
#    Generate at: https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords
# 6. Keep DATABASE_URL secure - it contains full database credentials
# 7. JWT_SECRET and MESSAGE_ENCRYPTION_KEY must be cryptographically random
#    Generate with: openssl rand -base64 32
# 8. Store production secrets in Vercel Environment Variables
# 9. Never share or expose these values in logs or error messages
# 10. Use .gitignore to ensure .env is never committed

# ========================================
# SUPABASE SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# ========================================
# 1. Go to https://supabase.com and create a new project
# 2. Copy your project URL and API keys from Settings > API
# 3. NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL: Your project's API URL
# 4. NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY: Your project's anon/public key
# 5. SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY: Your project's service_role key (keep secret!)
# 6. Enable Realtime for your tables in Database > Replication
# 7. Run the SQL migrations to create the messaging tables
